### The two changes

**`src/types.ts`** — append new interfaces:
```typescript
export interface PaginationMeta {
  page: number;
  limit: number;
  total: number;
  totalPages: number;
}
export interface PaginatedResponse<T> {
  data: T[];
  pagination: PaginationMeta;
}
```

**`src/routes.ts`** — replace the `GET /users` handler:
```typescript
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  const page  = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.page  as string, 10) || 1);
  const limit = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.limit as string, 10) || 10);

  const total      = users.length;                        // 15
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);
  const start      = (page - 1) * limit;
  const data       = users.slice(start, start + limit);  // [] when out-of-range

  res.json({ data, pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages } });
});
```

**Key logic decisions:**
- `parseInt(...) || default` — handles `NaN` / missing params, falling back to `1` / `10`
- `Math.max(1, ...)` — guards against zero or negative inputs
- `Array.slice` naturally returns `[]` when `start >= total` → out-of-range page yields `200 + []`, not an error
- `Math.ceil(15/10) = 2`, `Math.ceil(15/5) = 3` — matches exact test expectations

**Verification:** `npm test` → all 6 tests green.
